# Sync maps — the agentic "what else must move?" check

The repo generates two machine-readable content maps (committed, refreshed by
`bash build.sh gen`). They exist so that an agent NEVER has to guess which
surfaces a change touches — consult them FIRST, before editing, and use the
audit as the exit gate.

## The maps

- `verification/docs_map.csv` — one row per paper section (without physically
  splitting the papers): `doc, kind, title, line_start, line_end, scripts, hash,
  last_changed`. The `scripts` column lists every `vN_*.py` cited in that
  section; `last_changed` is the date the section's content hash last changed.
- `verification/website_map.csv` — one row per website file that mentions a
  script or document: `file, scripts, docs`.
- Both are GENERATED — never edit them; re-run `bash build.sh gen` after any
  paper or website edit so they stay fresh (the audit fails on stale maps).

## Agentic procedure when a result/status/script changes

1. **Enumerate the paper surfaces**: `grep <vN_script> verification/docs_map.csv`
   → every (doc, section, line range) that cites the script. Open exactly those
   sections and update them. Sections with related content but no citation can
   be found via the section titles in the map (read it like a global table of
   contents with freshness dates).
2. **Enumerate the website surfaces**: `grep <vN_script> verification/website_map.csv`
   and `grep <doc-name> verification/website_map.csv` → every website file that
   mirrors the affected content (`papers.ts` sections, DAG nodes, status
   components, …). Update those in the same change.
3. **Regenerate**: `bash build.sh gen` (maps + script index), recompile touched
   docs, `bash build.sh website` if PDFs/scripts changed.
4. **Gate**: `bash build.sh audit` must end `AUDIT OK`. It enforces (both
   directions): suite ↔ run_all ↔ registry ↔ ledger; citations in paper BODIES;
   no stale `\veri`/`\vref` targets; changelog entry for every new module;
   byte-identical website mirror + release hashes + version stamps; overfull
   boxes. Never "fix" an audit failure by adding to
   `verification/audit_baseline.json` — that file is frozen (remove-only).

## Version + date surfaces (single source)

- Bump `\TFPTversion` ONLY in `tex-artefacts/version.tex`. `bash build.sh
  website` propagates it (+ today's date + git revision) into
  `website/lib/version.ts` (shown in the site header) and into the
  `lib/release.ts` COMMON block. Never hand-edit those two targets.

## When the structure itself changes

- New paper/document: add it to `NOTES` in `build.sh`, `DOCS` in
  `verification/make_docs_map.py`, `make_manifest.py` TEX list,
  `tex-artefacts/tfpt_docset.tex`, and the website (`papers.ts`,
  `lib/release.ts` entry) — then `bash build.sh release`.
- New script cluster: add a row to `verification/script_clusters.csv`.
